            <title>[SPARK-2796] DecisionTree bug with ordered categorical features</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-2796</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In DecisionTree, the method sequentialBinSearchForOrderedCategoricalFeatureInClassification() indexed bins from 0 to (math.pow(2, featureCategories.toInt - 1) - 1).  This upper bound is the bound for unordered categorical features, not ordered ones.  The upper bound should be the arity (i.e., max value) of the feature.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
